# PRD‑quran‑sunnah‑companion.mdc

## 1 · Purpose

Provide practising Muslims a seamless way to listen to Qur’an, read Sahih Hadith, and perform Dhikr while browsing—without distractions or privacy trade‑offs.

## 2 · Objectives & Success Metrics

| Objective        | KPI                  | Target                     |
| ---------------- | -------------------- | -------------------------- |
| Quick activation | Install → 1st play   | ≥ 70 %                     |
| Retention        | 7‑day retained users | ≥ 25 %                     |
| Engagement       | Avg. daily playback  | ≥ 10 min                   |
| Quality          | Web Store rating     | ≥ 4.5⭐ & flag‑rate < 0.5 % |

## 3 · User Stories

1️⃣ As a user, I choose a reciter and hit **Play** so I can listen while reading.
2️⃣ As a user, I see a new Sahih Hadith every hour so I learn continuously.
3️⃣ As a user, I receive Dhikr prompts at custom intervals so I remember Allah.
4️⃣ As an Arabic‑only user, I switch UI language to Arabic.
5️⃣ As a busy user, I snooze all prompts until Fajr.

## 4 · Functional Requirements

* **Popup dashboard** with three equal cards (Qur’an, Hadith, Dhikr).
* **Audio** continues via `chrome.offscreen`.
* **APIs**: api.quran.com, hadithapi.com (Sahih collections), fitrahive/dua‑dhikr.
* **Scheduling**: `chrome.alarms`, quiet hours respected.
* **Translations**: Arabic & English toggle.
* **Data storage**: `chrome.storage.sync`, ≤ 100 KB.

## 5 · Non‑functional

* Manifest V3; CSP hardened.
* Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS; no external frameworks runtime.
* Lighthouse PWA score ≥ 90.
* Halal‑compliant visuals; no faces.

